text:
Hi,

in the source file srclib/apr/locks/beos/thread_cond.c (lines 116-120), I discovered the following bit of code:


    if (rv != B_OK)
        if (rv == B_TIMED_OUT)
            return APR_TIMEUP;
        return rv;

Since there are no brackets, the "return rv;" is unconditionally executed.  This behaviour does not match the indentation of the code and seems to be unintended.  So one of the following actions should be taken:

1) either modify the given code to read as follows:


    if (rv != B_OK) {
        if (rv == B_TIMED_OUT)
            return APR_TIMEUP;
        return rv;
    }

I believe that this is the correct fix.

2) or change the indentation to reflect the real behaviour and remove the, then useless, code after the "return rv;".

I hope this helps,
Jochen

PS.: the email address used for this account is a one-time address and is not monitored by me.
